05/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- One man killed and more than 30 people were injured on Sunday (October 4th) in the southwest town of Siroki Brijeg, ahead of a match between a local football club and a Sarajevo squad.
According to local media, clashes broke out as soon as the Sarajevo team's fans arrived in town to watch the game.
Six of the injured are in serious condition.
Shops, restaurants and private homes near the stadium, as well as cars and police vehicles, were damaged.
Special police forces from Mostar arrived in Siroki Brijeg to reinforce local police, using tear gas and water cannons to disperse the crowd.
The match was cancelled.
High Representative Valentin Inzko condemned the violence and insisted all those responsible face justice.
(RTRS, Fena, Pincom.info, Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz, AP, Reuters - 04/10/09)
